TOPIC: ~german_proficiency (German Deutsch)

t: ( ~german ) Most programs offered by Hamburg University are taught in German you need to provide proof of German language proficiency to be admitted; detailed information about the level of German language proficiency required and about the certificates accepted by Hamburg University is provided <a href="https://www.uni-hamburg.de/en/campuscenter/bewerbung/international/studium-mit-abschluss/sprachkenntnisse/deutschkenntnisse.html" target="_blank">here</a>. Are you interested in learning the German language?
  a: ( ~yes ) Universit√§t Hamburg does not offer any preparatory German courses. If you are planning to come to Germany in order to learn German, you can find information about that on the website of the <a href="https://www.daad.de/deutschland/nach-deutschland/voraussetzungen/en/6221-german-language" target="_blank">DAAD</a> (German Academic Exchange Service).<br>
  The DAAD also provides a database of German courses offered throughout Germany: https://www.daad.de/deutschland/studienangebote/sommerkurse/en/ Information on courses offered in Hamburg can be found via the following <a href="http://hamburg.kursportal.info" target="_blank">course portal</a>.<br><br>

  If you are planning to acquire the necessary German language skills in your home country or in other countries, you can find information about that on the <a href="https://www.goethe.de/en/spr/kup/kur/wwt.html" target="_blank">Goethe-Institute's website</a>.

  a: ( ~no ) Ok. In that case please find an overview of the programs taught in English <a href="https://www.uni-hamburg.de/en/campuscenter/studienangebot.html#65,98,115,99,104,108,117,115,115,61,111,112,116,51,38,70,97,107,117,108,116,97,101,116,61,38,115,111,114,116,61,83,112,114,97,99,104,101,38,115,111,114,116,45,100,105,114,61,117,112,38,105,110,100,101,120,61" target="_blank">here</a>. <br><br>

